A speakeasy café opposite Kuala Terengganu City Centre (KTCC). It is run by the friendliest people who share a passion for great coffee. They even roast their own beans as you'd be able to see from the roaster housed in the back. I ordered the iced mocha and before I review it, I need you to understand that I'm the sort of person who normally sweetens my lattes and mochas to drown out the coffee's acidity—which happens quite a fair bit. I didn't need to do that here at the Octagon Café. The coffee was so smooth and oh, so delicious. The kind that makes you see colour in flowers again; that makes you feel like that person on a TV-sitcom enjoying a hot one while it's snowing outside. Magical, in other words. To go with the wizardry-infused beverage, I ordered their berries cream cheese bar. A fruity-sort of brownie that was rich but not overbearing. It was great, but in retrospect, would go better with tea instead—it makes me curious to try the lemon cream bar on my next visit. There are no non-dairy alternatives. Understandable, as I don't believe barista-grade almond/soy/oat milk are as accessible in Terengganu as they would be in Kuala Lumpur. The inside can feel a little stuffy and because there're no open windows or the like, the sound inside the café bounces around and may get overwhelming if it's a full house. That aside, RM10 for the iced mocha, RM10 for the brownie, and you got yourself a splendid experience. If you find yourself in Kuala Terengganu, give these coffee wizards a try.
